+        # M363 CRITICAL: When ZeRO >= 1 is active, NEVER skip gradient AllReduce.
+        # ZeRO-1 partitions optimizer states across ranks. Each rank owns 1/N of
+        # Adam m/v and only updates its partition. It MUST receive the fully-reduced
+        # gradient every step. Skipping causes NCCL sequence number mismatch:
+        #   rank 0 enqueues AllReduce for its partition buckets,
+        #   rank 1,2 don't → NCCL timeout at SeqNum divergence.
+        # Crash evidence: Phase 7c Kx=64, rank0 enqueued=166 vs rank1,2 enqueued=133.
+        #
+        # DES-LOC Kx gating only applies to PARAMETER averaging (handled separately
+        # in desloc_post_step / the user's training loop), not gradient reduction.
+        # With ZeRO-0: skip gradient AR on non-Kx steps → each rank has full opt state.
+        # With ZeRO-1+: gradient AR every step → param averaging at Kx boundaries.
